6. Transfer of Lien. Contractor transfers and assigns to Lender, and to Lender's
successors and assigns, all of Contractor's rights to receive the Contract Sum due
hereunder, together with valid, first, and superior liens as created in this Construction
Contract to secure payment of the amount hereby transferred and Lender is subrogated
to, all the lien rights and equities of Contractor pertaining to the amount transferred.
Lender-does not assume any obligations imposed upon Contractor by virtue of this
Construction Contract and shall not be liable for the performance of or breach thereof
by Contractor.
Completion by Contractor, but not Lender. Contractor shall be obligated to complete
all werk in accordance with the Construction Contract documents, but Lender shall not
be responsible for the completion of the improvements and shall not in any manner be
considered a guarantor of performance by Contractor. Contractor agrees to indemnify
and hold Lender-harinless against all claims for completion of the improvements.
8. Partial Lien- In the event the improvements are not completed by Contractor according
to the plans and specifications, and, for whatever reason, it is determined that Lender
does not have a lien to the extent of the full amount of the original principal amount of
the Note, then Leader shall have a valid lien for the Contract Sum, less the amount
reasonably necessary to complete-the improvements according to the plans and
specifications, or in such event Lender, at its option, shall have the right to complete
the improvements, and the lien shall be valid for the Contract Sum.
9. Alterations and Extras. No alterations, additions, or deletions shall be made in the work
shown or described by the drawings and-specifications, nor shall any extra work,
additions, or materials be charged or paid forl unless a separate estimate for such extra
work is submitted in writing by Contractor to Owner and agreed to in writing by them
and approved in writing by Lender before the extra work is started. The additional
amount to be paid for all the extra work, additions, and materials so agreed to and
furnished shall be a part of the indebredness secured by the lien created by this
Construction Contract; no other documentishall be/necessary in order to evidence or
secure such additional indebtedness. Lender, at its option and subject to the execution
of such additional loan documents as it might require, may advance all or part of such
additional amount. If no such arrangement has been made, Owner shall pay Contractor
in cash upon completion of such extra work and Contractor shall have a lien on the
property for the payment of such amount, which hen Contractor agrees shall be
subordinate to the lien retained and transferred to Lender in this Construction Contract.
All extra work done or material furnished without such written change order shall be
considered as performed under the original Construction Contract and no extra
payment shall be demanded or allowed.
10. Receipts and Releases. Upon request Contractor shall furnish Owner er hender proper
receipts and releases from any and all subcontractors, workmen, and suppliers, so that
no liens may be fixed upon the property except the express lien created by this
Construction Contract.
